AutoBuiltDocumentedBuilder
public interface DocumentedBuilder<T> extends Builder<T>
A Builder which provides additional information about its capability. Namely, it provides its name, the type of the built objects, the param it takes, and the method it has been built from.

    • alias

      default DocumentedBuilder<T> alias(Alias alias)
      Returns a new DocumentedBuilder that is an alias of this builder. The new builder has name dictated by alias.name() and uses this builder as dictated by alias.value(). Optionally, can define new params that are passed to this builder through alias.passThroughParams().
      Parameters:
      alias - the alias to apply
      Returns:
      a new DocumentedBuilder
